article.headline: Stetson 69, Jacksonville 57
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Senior guard Anthony Register scored a game-high 17 points Thursday to lead Stetson to a 69-57 victory over Jacksonville. Stetson won for the second time in as many games since snapping a 15-game losing streak that included 10 losses this season. The Hatters improved to 2-2 in Atlantic Sun Conference action. Jacksonville lost its eighth straight game, falling to 1-10 overall and 1-3 in conference. Register made all eight of his free throws to lead a Hatter squad that converted 21 of 25 shots from the charity stripe. Fellow senior guard E.J. Gordon added four of five free throws in his 14-point, eight-rebound effort. Jacksonville junior center Ljubisa Vrcelj had 14 points and seven rebounds for the Dolphins, who also got 13 points from senior small forward Antonio Cool and 10 points from freshman forward Marcus Allen. Stetson led 34-26 at the half largely due to the play of reserve forward Garfield Blair, who came off the bench to score seven points in eight minutes. Hatter reserves outscored Jacksonville's bench 14-8 in the first 20 minutes. The Dolphins were within four points, trailing 47-43 with 9:17 to play, when the Hatters went on a 13-4 run that sealed the victory. Gordon led the charge with nine of Stetson's 13 points in the run.
